</tbody>
</table>
<p data-index="611">With the bond premium of $24,000, Buchanan amortizes $1,200 to interest expense each period for <span data-index="612">20 periods ($24,000 ÷ 20)</span>.</p>
<p data-index="613">Buchanan records the first semiannual interest payment of <math alttext="mathml" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" overflow="scroll" data-index="614"><mrow data-index="615"><mi mathvariant="normal" data-index="616">$</mi><mn data-index="617">40,000</mn><mtext data-index="618">&nbsp;</mtext><mrow data-index="619"><mo data-index="620">(</mo><mi mathvariant="normal" data-index="621">$</mi><mn data-index="622">800,000</mn><mo data-index="623">×</mo><mn data-index="624">.10</mn><mo data-index="625">×</mo><mfrac bevelled="true" data-index="626"><mn data-index="627">6</mn><mn data-index="628">12</mn></mfrac><mo data-index="629">)</mo></mrow></mrow></math> and the bond premium on July 1, 2020, as follows.</p>

