<p data-index="864">The Interest Expense account now contains a debit balance of $16,000, which represents the proper amount of interest expense—four months at 6 percent on $800,000.</p>
<p data-index="865">The illustration above was simplified by having the January 1, 2020, bonds issued on March 1, 2020, <b data-index="866">at par</b>. If, however, Taft issued the 6 percent bonds at 102, its March 1 entry would be:</p>
