<h4 data-index="1485"><span class="blue" data-index="1486">Bonds Issued at a Premium</span></h4>
<p data-index="1487">Now assume that for the previous bond issue by Evermaster Corporation, investors are willing to accept an effective-interest rate of 6 percent. In that case, they would pay $108,530 or a premium of $8,530, computed as shown in <a class="blue" href="#c14-fig-0007" id="c14-fig-0007-1" data-index="1488" data-section-index="24" data-section-idref="c14-fig-0007" data-target-data-index="1490"><b data-index="1489">Illustration 14.7</b></a>.</p>
<figure id="c14-fig-0007" data-index="1490">

<div style=" background-color: #FFFDE5; padding: 1em; border: 1px solid #000;" data-index="1491">
<table class="bordernone" style=" width: 100%;" data-index="1492">
<tbody data-index="1493">
<tr data-index="1494">
